## 1. Network layout (recommended)

| Device | Role | IP (example) |
|--------|------|----------------|
| **MikroTik hAP²** | Gateway, DHCP, hotspot, Wi‑Fi AP | `192.168.88.1/24` |
| **HP ProBook (Ubuntu)** | Laravel portal, MariaDB, FreeRADIUS | `192.168.88.2/24` |
| **Students (Wi‑Fi)** | Hotspot clients | `192.168.88.0/24` (DHCP) |

Physical wiring:

1. **ISP / upstream** → MikroTik **WAN** port (ether1 on most hAP models).
2. **HP ProBook Ethernet** → MikroTik **LAN** port (bridge member, e.g. ether2).
3. Leave the ProBook on **AC power**; treat it as an always-on server (UPS recommended).

```text
[ Internet ] ──► [ MikroTik hAP² 192.168.88.1 ] ──► Wi‑Fi clients
                      │
                      └── ether2 ──► [ HP ProBook 192.168.88.2 ]
                                         Laravel + MariaDB + FreeRADIUS
```

