## 2. HP ProBook — fresh Ubuntu Server

### 2.1 Install Ubuntu

1. Download **Ubuntu Server 24.04 LTS** (64-bit) from [ubuntu.com/download/server](https://ubuntu.com/download/server).
2. Create a bootable USB (Rufus on Windows, or `dd` on Linux).
3. Boot the ProBook from USB → **Install Ubuntu Server**.
4. During install:
   - Hostname: `tesnet-server`
   - Create user: e.g. `tesnet` (note the password).
   - Enable **OpenSSH server**.
   - Optional: guided LVM with most of the disk for `/`.
5. Reboot, log in, run updates:

```bash
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo reboot
```

### 2.2 Static IP (Netplan)

Edit netplan (interface name may be `enp0s31f6`, `eno1`, etc. — check with `ip link`):

```bash
ip link
sudo nano /etc/netplan/00-installer-config.yaml
```

Example (adjust `enp0s31f6` to your interface):

```yaml
network:
  version: 2
  ethernets:
    enp0s31f6:
      dhcp4: no
      addresses:
        - 192.168.88.2/24
      routes:
        - to: default
          via: 192.168.88.1
      nameservers:
        addresses:
          - 192.168.88.1
          - 8.8.8.8
```

Apply:

```bash
sudo netplan apply
ip a
ping -c 3 192.168.88.1
```

### 2.3 Firewall (UFW)

Allow SSH, HTTP/S, and RADIUS from the MikroTik only:

```bash
sudo ufw default deny incoming
sudo ufw default allow outgoing
sudo ufw allow OpenSSH
sudo ufw allow from 192.168.88.0/24 to any port 80,443 proto tcp
sudo ufw allow from 192.168.88.1 to any port 1812,1813 proto udp
sudo ufw enable
sudo ufw status
```

### 2.4 Install software stack

```bash
sudo apt install -y software-properties-common curl git unzip \
  apache2 mariadb-server mariadb-client \
  freeradius freeradius-mysql freeradius-utils \
  php8.3 php8.3-cli php8.3-fpm php8.3-mysql php8.3-xml php8.3-mbstring \
  php8.3-curl php8.3-zip php8.3-bcmath php8.3-intl libapache2-mod-php8.3
```

Install **Composer**:

```bash
curl -sS https://getcomposer.org/installer | php
sudo mv composer.phar /usr/local/bin/composer
composer --version
```

Install **Node.js 20** (for building portal assets):

```bash
curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | sudo -E bash -
sudo apt install -y nodejs
node --version
npm --version
```

Enable Apache modules:

```bash
sudo a2enmod rewrite ssl headers
sudo systemctl enable --now apache2 mariadb
```

