## 3. MariaDB — shared database for Laravel + FreeRADIUS

### 3.1 Secure MariaDB and create database

```bash
sudo mysql_secure_installation
```

Create DB and user (replace `STRONG_DB_PASSWORD`):

```bash
sudo mysql
```

```sql
CREATE DATABASE tesnet CHARACTER SET utf8mb4 COLLATE utf8mb4_unicode_ci;
CREATE USER 'tesnet'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'STRONG_DB_PASSWORD';
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON tesnet.* TO 'tesnet'@'localhost';
FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
EXIT;
```

### 3.2 FreeRADIUS → SQL (same `tesnet` database)

Edit SQL module:

```bash
sudo nano /etc/freeradius/3.0/mods-available/sql
```

Set (inside the `sql { ... }` block):

```conf
dialect = "mysql"
driver = "rlm_sql_mysql"
server = "localhost"
port = 3306
login = "tesnet"
password = "STRONG_DB_PASSWORD"
radius_db = "tesnet"
```

Enable SQL and disable default file auth for production:

```bash
sudo ln -sf /etc/freeradius/3.0/mods-available/sql /etc/freeradius/3.0/mods-enabled/sql
sudo rm -f /etc/freeradius/3.0/mods-enabled/eap
```

Edit the default site to use SQL for authorize/accounting:

```bash
sudo nano /etc/freeradius/3.0/sites-available/default
```

In **`authorize`** section, ensure `sql` is present (uncomment if needed):

```conf
authorize {
    ...
    sql
    ...
}
```

In **`accounting`** section:

```conf
accounting {
    ...
    sql
    ...
}
```

In **`post-auth`** section (optional but recommended):

```conf
post-auth {
    ...
    sql
    ...
}
```

### 3.3 RADIUS client — MikroTik NAS

Pick a long shared secret (same value goes on the router later):

```bash
sudo nano /etc/freeradius/3.0/clients.conf
```

Add at the end:

```conf
client mikrotik-hap {
    ipaddr          = 192.168.88.1
    secret          = "CHANGE_ME_RADIUS_SECRET"
    require_message_authenticator = true
    limit_proxy_state = true
    nas_type        = other
}
```

Use a long random secret (32+ characters). Required for FreeRADIUS 3.2+ BlastRADIUS hardening with RouterOS 7.x.

Test config and start RADIUS:

```bash
sudo freeradius -CX
sudo systemctl enable --now freeradius
sudo systemctl status freeradius
```

