## 4. Deploy TesNet (Laravel)

### 4.1 Copy application files

From your dev machine, clone or copy the repo to the server, e.g.:

```bash
sudo mkdir -p /var/www
sudo chown $USER:$USER /var/www
cd /var/www
git clone https://github.com/reginaldtesla/MiniISP-Landing-page.git
cd MiniISP-Landing-page/TesNet
```

Clone URL: `https://github.com/reginaldtesla/MiniISP-Landing-page.git` — default folder **`MiniISP-Landing-page`**, app path **`MiniISP-Landing-page/TesNet`**.

Or upload the `TesNet/` folder with `scp` / WinSCP to `/var/www/MiniISP-Landing-page/TesNet`.

### 4.2 Install PHP dependencies and build assets

```bash
cd /var/www/MiniISP-Landing-page/TesNet
composer install --no-dev --optimize-autoloader
cp .env.example .env
php artisan key:generate
```

Edit `.env` for production (minimum):

```env
APP_NAME=TesNet
APP_ENV=production
APP_DEBUG=false
APP_URL=https://portal.tesnet.local
APP_FORCE_HTTPS=true

DB_CONNECTION=mariadb
DB_HOST=127.0.0.1
DB_PORT=3306
DB_DATABASE=tesnet
DB_USERNAME=tesnet
DB_PASSWORD=STRONG_DB_PASSWORD

ADMIN_PHONE=0550000001
ADMIN_PASSWORD=ChangeThisAdminPassword
ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@tesnet.local

MIKROTIK_LOGIN_URL=http://192.168.88.1/login

PAYSTACK_PUBLIC_KEY=pk_live_...
PAYSTACK_SECRET_KEY=sk_live_...
PAYSTACK_CUSTOMER_EMAIL_DOMAIN=billing.yourdomain.com

SUPPORT_PHONE=0551234567
SUPPORT_EMAIL=support@yourdomain.com
SUPPORT_HOURS="Monday–Friday, 8:00 AM – 5:00 PM"
```

Run migrations (creates Laravel tables **and** `radcheck` / `radreply` / `radacct`):

```bash
php artisan migrate --force
php artisan db:seed --force
npm install
npm run build:offline
```

Set permissions:

```bash
sudo chown -R www-data:www-data /var/www/MiniISP-Landing-page/TesNet/storage /var/www/MiniISP-Landing-page/TesNet/bootstrap/cache
sudo chmod -R 775 /var/www/MiniISP-Landing-page/TesNet/storage /var/www/MiniISP-Landing-page/TesNet/bootstrap/cache
```

**Offline UI assets (fonts + icons):** `build:offline` writes self-contained files to `public/assets/portal/`:

| File / folder | Contents |
|---------------|----------|
| `portal.css` | Tailwind + all styles |
| `fonts/` | Inter, Hanken Grotesk, JetBrains Mono, Material Symbols (icons) |
| `portal-theme.js` | Dark / light mode |
| `portal-announcements.js` | Dashboard announcement modal |
| `portal-custom-calculator.js` | Buy Data custom amount slider |

Keep `PORTAL_USE_OFFLINE_ASSETS=true` in `.env` (default). The portal and admin hub then **never** load Google Fonts, CDNs, or the Vite dev server — only your Apache host.

Re-run `npm run build:offline` after any CSS, JS, or Blade style change before deploying.

### 4.3 Apache virtual host

```bash
sudo nano /etc/apache2/sites-available/tesnet.conf
```

```apache
<VirtualHost *:80>
    ServerName portal.tesnet.local
    DocumentRoot /var/www/MiniISP-Landing-page/TesNet/public

    <Directory /var/www/MiniISP-Landing-page/TesNet/public>
        AllowOverride All
        Require all granted
    </Directory>

    ErrorLog ${APACHE_LOG_DIR}/tesnet-error.log
    CustomLog ${APACHE_LOG_DIR}/tesnet-access.log combined
</VirtualHost>
```

Enable site:

```bash
sudo a2ensite tesnet.conf
sudo a2dissite 000-default.conf
sudo systemctl reload apache2
```

For **HTTPS** (required for Paystack live webhooks), use Let’s Encrypt if you have a public domain, or an internal CA / self-signed cert for LAN-only testing:

```bash
sudo apt install -y certbot python3-certbot-apache
sudo certbot --apache -d portal.yourdomain.com
```

Set `APP_URL` to the exact HTTPS URL students use. Webhook URL:

```text
https://portal.yourdomain.com/portal/payments/webhook
```

See [`docs/PAYSTACK.md`](docs/PAYSTACK.md).

### 4.4 Cron (Laravel scheduler)

```bash
sudo crontab -u www-data -e
```

Add:

```cron
* * * * * cd /var/www/MiniISP-Landing-page/TesNet && php artisan schedule:run >> /dev/null 2>&1
```

This runs scheduled tasks defined in `routes/console.php`:

| Command | Schedule | Purpose |
|---------|----------|---------|
| `tesnet:backup-database` | Daily 02:30 | MariaDB dump → `storage/backups/` |
| `tesnet:monitor` | Every 5 min | Health checks → `storage/logs/monitor.log` |

Manual test: `php artisan tesnet:monitor` and `php artisan tesnet:backup-database`.

Set `LOG_CHANNEL=daily` in production for Laravel log rotation. See [`docs/PRODUCTION_CHECKLIST.md`](docs/PRODUCTION_CHECKLIST.md) and [`docs/DAILY_OPERATIONS.md`](docs/DAILY_OPERATIONS.md).

