## 7. Production checklist

**HP ProBook (Ubuntu)**

- [ ] Static IP `192.168.88.2`, gateway `192.168.88.1`
- [ ] MariaDB `tesnet` database, strong passwords
- [ ] FreeRADIUS running, SQL enabled, MikroTik client configured
- [ ] Laravel `.env` production values, `php artisan migrate --seed`
- [ ] Apache (or nginx) + **HTTPS** + correct `APP_URL`
- [ ] Paystack webhook URL registered ([`docs/PAYSTACK.md`](docs/PAYSTACK.md))
- [ ] `npm run build:offline` run; `public/assets/portal/portal.css` and `fonts/` present on server
- [ ] `PORTAL_USE_OFFLINE_ASSETS=true` in `.env`
- [ ] Backups scheduled for MariaDB (`mysqldump tesnet`)

**MikroTik hAP²**

- [ ] WAN on ether1, NAT masquerade
- [ ] Bridge LAN + Wi‑Fi AP, DHCP pool `192.168.88.10–254`
- [ ] Hotspot on bridge, `use-radius=yes`, accounting on
- [ ] RADIUS → `192.168.88.2`, secret matches `clients.conf`
- [ ] Anti-leak config done: §5.7 Steps 1–7 (walled garden, no trial, no bypass bindings)
- [ ] Router admin (Winbox/API) **not** open to whole hotspot LAN (§5.7 Step 6)
- [ ] `login.html` redirects to Laravel portal (not legacy PHPNuxBill)
- [ ] Router admin / Winbox / API restricted to management IPs

**TesNet app**

- [ ] `MIKROTIK_LOGIN_URL=http://192.168.88.1/login` (or your hotspot login path)
- [ ] Admin password changed from seed default
- [ ] Packages created with correct data, speed, and validity type
- [ ] Support phone/email set in `.env`

